[{"id":"exponents-st-e1","diff":"easy","type":"mc","q":"<p>Simplify: 5<sup>6</sup> &divide; 5<sup>2</sup></p>","info":"","qa":"","qb":"","choices":["5<sup>3</sup>","5<sup>4</sup>","5<sup>8</sup>","5<sup>12</sup>","25<sup>4</sup>"],"answer":1,"tol":0,"explain":"<p>When dividing powers with the same base, subtract exponents: 5<sup>6&minus;2</sup> = 5<sup>4</sup>.</p>"},
{"id":"exponents-st-e2","diff":"easy","type":"mc","q":"<p>Which of the following equals (x<sup>3</sup>)<sup>4</sup>?</p>","info":"","qa":"","qb":"","choices":["x<sup>7</sup>","x<sup>12</sup>","x<sup>34</sup>","x<sup>81</sup>","x<sup>64</sup>"],"answer":1,"tol":0,"explain":"<p>Power of a power: multiply exponents. (x<sup>3</sup>)<sup>4</sup> = x<sup>3&times;4</sup> = x<sup>12</sup>.</p>"},
{"id":"exponents-st-e3","diff":"easy","type":"ne","q":"<p>Evaluate &radic;121 + &radic;36.</p>","info":"","qa":"","qb":"","choices":[],"answer":17,"tol":0,"explain":"<p>&radic;121 = 11 and &radic;36 = 6. Their sum is 11 + 6 = 17.</p>"},
{"id":"exponents-st-e4","diff":"easy","type":"mc","q":"<p>Express 3<sup>-2</sup> as a fraction.</p>","info":"","qa":"","qb":"","choices":["-9","-6","1/6","1/9","2/3"],"answer":3,"tol":0,"explain":"<p>A negative exponent gives the reciprocal: 3<sup>-2</sup> = 1/3<sup>2</sup> = 1/9.</p>"},
{"id":"exponents-st-m1","diff":"medium","type":"mc","q":"<p>The number 0.00056 written in scientific notation is:</p>","info":"","qa":"","qb":"","choices":["5.6 &times; 10<sup>-4</sup>","5.6 &times; 10<sup>-3</sup>","56 &times; 10<sup>-5</sup>","5.6 &times; 10<sup>4</sup>","0.56 &times; 10<sup>-3</sup>"],"answer":0,"tol":0,"explain":"<p>Move the decimal point 4 places to the right to get 5.6, so 0.00056 = 5.6 &times; 10<sup>-4</sup>.</p>"},
{"id":"exponents-st-m2","diff":"medium","type":"mc","q":"<p>Simplify &radic;75 + &radic;27.</p>","info":"","qa":"","qb":"","choices":["8&radic;3","5&radic;3","2&radic;102","8&radic;6","102&radic;3"],"answer":0,"tol":0,"explain":"<p>&radic;75 = &radic;(25&times;3) = 5&radic;3 and &radic;27 = &radic;(9&times;3) = 3&radic;3. Sum: 5&radic;3 + 3&radic;3 = 8&radic;3.</p>"},
{"id":"exponents-st-m3","diff":"medium","type":"ne","q":"<p>Evaluate 27<sup>2/3</sup>.</p>","info":"","qa":"","qb":"","choices":[],"answer":9,"tol":0,"explain":"<p>27<sup>2/3</sup> = (27<sup>1/3</sup>)<sup>2</sup> = (cube root of 27)<sup>2</sup> = 3<sup>2</sup> = 9.</p>"},
{"id":"exponents-st-m4","diff":"medium","type":"mc","q":"<p>Rationalize the denominator: 10/&radic;5.</p>","info":"","qa":"","qb":"","choices":["2&radic;5","&radic;5","10&radic;5","5&radic;2","2"],"answer":0,"tol":0,"explain":"<p>Multiply numerator and denominator by &radic;5: (10&radic;5)/5 = 2&radic;5.</p>"},
{"id":"exponents-st-m5","diff":"medium","type":"qc","q":"","info":"x is a number with 0 < x < 1.","qa":"x<sup>3</sup>","qb":"x<sup>1/3</sup>","choices":[],"answer":1,"tol":0,"explain":"<p>For 0 &lt; x &lt; 1, raising to a power greater than 1 makes the value smaller, while taking a root (power less than 1) makes it larger. Thus x<sup>3</sup> &lt; x &lt; x<sup>1/3</sup>, so Quantity B is greater. Answer: B.</p>"},
{"id":"exponents-st-h1","diff":"hard","type":"qc","q":"","info":"","qa":"4<sup>50</sup>","qb":"2<sup>101</sup>","choices":[],"answer":1,"tol":0,"explain":"<p>Rewrite with a common base: 4<sup>50</sup> = (2<sup>2</sup>)<sup>50</sup> = 2<sup>100</sup>. Quantity B is 2<sup>101</sup> = 2 &times; 2<sup>100</sup>, which is larger. Answer: B.</p>"},
{"id":"exponents-st-h2","diff":"hard","type":"ne","q":"<p>If 9<sup>2x-1</sup> = 27<sup>x+1</sup>, what is the value of x?</p>","info":"","qa":"","qb":"","choices":[],"answer":5,"tol":0,"explain":"<p>Write both sides with base 3: 9<sup>2x-1</sup> = 3<sup>2(2x-1)</sup> = 3<sup>4x-2</sup> and 27<sup>x+1</sup> = 3<sup>3(x+1)</sup> = 3<sup>3x+3</sup>. Set exponents equal: 4x - 2 = 3x + 3, so x = 5.</p>"},
{"id":"exponents-st-h3","diff":"hard","type":"ms","q":"<p>Which of the following expressions are equal to 16<sup>3</sup>? Select all that apply.</p>","info":"","qa":"","qb":"","choices":["2<sup>12</sup>","4<sup>6</sup>","8<sup>4</sup>","64<sup>2</sup>","2<sup>10</sup>"],"answer":[0,1,2,3],"tol":0,"explain":"<p>16<sup>3</sup> = (2<sup>4</sup>)<sup>3</sup> = 2<sup>12</sup> = 4096. Check each: 2<sup>12</sup> = 4096 (yes); 4<sup>6</sup> = (2<sup>2</sup>)<sup>6</sup> = 2<sup>12</sup> = 4096 (yes); 8<sup>4</sup> = (2<sup>3</sup>)<sup>4</sup> = 2<sup>12</sup> = 4096 (yes); 64<sup>2</sup> = (2<sup>6</sup>)<sup>2</sup> = 2<sup>12</sup> = 4096 (yes); 2<sup>10</sup> = 1024 (no). The correct choices are 2<sup>12</sup>, 4<sup>6</sup>, 8<sup>4</sup>, and 64<sup>2</sup>.</p>"}]
